data.title: William Russell Obituary - St. Johns, Michigan
data.meta_description: William Sherwood Russell died Saturday, March 28, 2015 at the age of 78. He was born December 30, 1936 in Owosso, MI the son of Sherwood R. Russell M.D. and Edith R. (Hunter) Russell.  William graduated from St. Johns Military Academy in Wisconsin in 1955 and continued his military career as a Nuclear Weapon Technician in the U.S. Air Force retiring in 1975. William earned his private pilotâ€™s license and enjoyed golfing, snow skiing and flying. He was a Ham Radio Operator and a member of VFW Post # 5670 in Gwinn, MI and the Masonic Lodge #101 in Marquette, MI. On August 31, 1956 he married Janet Hansen in New Hampshire and she survives him. Also surviving is a daughter, Kathleen (Gilbert A.) Baker of Fowler and grandson Ian Michael Baker. He was preceded in death by his parents and a son Sherwood Dean Russell.  Funeral services will be held 11:00 AM Wednesday, April 1, 2015 at Keck-Coleman Funeral Home, St. Johns with Rev. Dr. Joseph Mlaker officiating. Interment will follow at Mt. Rest Cemetery with military honors provided by the St. Johns Honor Guard. The family will receive relatives and friends 2:00 to 4:00 and 6:00 to 8:00 PM Tuesday, March 31, 2015 at the funeral home. A Masonic service will be held at 7:30 PM Tuesday at the funeral home. Memorials may be made to any Shriners Hospital for Children.
